The paper discusses the development of efficient methods for evaluating rankers, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses online learning and pairwise comparisons, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (AI) and data structures (DS), respectively. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on large-scale online ranker evaluation datasets, which suggests a potential application in human-computer interaction (HC).
